{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592724","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592724"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:19:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:19:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15278"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15278","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15278"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0.12,0.26,0.15,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7969"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65947"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7969","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7969"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15278"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51396"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"3382"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8124"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19392"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19394"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22038"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65947","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65947"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old woman presents with a one day history of severe epigastric pain radiating to the back, with associated nausea and vomiting. Her medical history includes hypertension and heart failure, for which she takes multiple medications.  She is a non-smoker and does not drink alcohol. She is diagnosed with acute pancreatitis. An ultrasound examination of her upper abdomen is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications may have been the cause of the acute pancreatitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Beta blockers","Loop diuretics","Thiazide diuretics","Potassium-sparing diuretics","Angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EGallstone disease is the underlying cause of the problem in 60% of cases of acute pancreatitis and excessive alcohol consumption is responsible for another 20%. Drug-induced pancreatitis is an important consideration in patients presenting with acute pancreatitis. There are a variety of other causes for the remaining 20% of cases. Among cardiovascular medications:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBeta blockers\u003C/strong\u003E rarely cause pancreatitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELoop diuretics\u003C/strong\u003E have not been consistently associated with pancreatitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThiazide diuretics\u003C/strong\u003E are known to cause acute pancreatitis as a rare but documented adverse effect\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPotassium-sparing diuretics\u003C/strong\u003E have not been linked to pancreatitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAngiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors\u003C/strong\u003E have very rarely been associated with pancreatitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe mechanism of thiazide-induced pancreatitis is not fully understood but may involve direct toxic effects on pancreatic tissue or immune-mediated inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Thiazide diuretics can cause acute pancreatitis as a rare but significant adverse effect","Drug-induced pancreatitis accounts for 0.1-2% of acute pancreatitis cases"],"references":["Patel DM, Patel MM, Patel LB, Patel VB, Patel MV, Patel DK. Diuretics-Induced Acute Pancreatitis: Case Series with a Review of the Literature. Curr Drug Saf. 2024 Oct 2. doi: 10.2174/0115748863324787240916114833. Epub ahead of print. PMID: 39360546.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51396"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15278"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51396"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T08:27:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T08:28:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7969"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65947"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"da